  "output": "## Test Coverage Analysis\n\n**Current state: 0%.** No `tests/` directory, no test framework in `requirements.txt`, and `find -iname \"*test*\"` across the repo turns up nothing. Every module below (`models.py`, `filters.py`, `store.py`, `pipeline.py`, `notify.py`, `fetchers.py`, `agent.py`, `cli.py`) is completely unexercised.\n\n### Suggested test infra (add to `requirements.txt` as dev deps)\n```\npytest>=8.0\npytest-asyncio>=0.24\nrespx>=0.21          # mock httpx transports for fetchers.py\nfreezegun>=1.5        # freeze time for posted_at / cutoff logic\n```\nLayout: `tests/test_models.py`, `tests/test_filters.py`, `tests/test_store.py`, `tests/test_pipeline.py`, `tests/test_notify.py`, `tests/test_fetchers.py`, `tests/test_agent.py`, plus `tests/conftest.py` for shared fixtures (a `Job` factory, an in-memory `Store`).\n\n---\n\n### 1. `models.py` â€” highest-value target, pure logic, zero deps\n\n**Untested:** `parse_posted_at`, `Job.key`, `Job.posted_dt`, `Job.content_hash`, `Job.to_row`.\n\n**Edge cases missed:**\n- Empty string / `None` input to `parse_posted_at`\n- Millisecond epoch vs second epoch boundary (exactly `1_000_000_000_000`)\n- Negative epoch (`s.lstrip(\"-\").isdigit()` path)\n- ISO string with trailing `Z`\n- ISO string with no timezone (naive) â€” should assume UTC\n- Garbage string (Workday's `\"Posted 3 Days Ago\"`) â†’ must return `None`, not raise\n- `content_hash` stability: same title/location/url/department â†’ same hash; changing `posted_at` or `salary_range` must NOT change hash (dedup would otherwise thrash)\n- `key` uniqueness across two jobs from different sources but same `external_id`\n\n```python\n# tests/test_models.py\nimport pytest\nfrom datetime import timezone\nfrom models import Job, parse_posted_at\n\n\nclass TestParsePostedAt:\n    def test_empty_returns_none(self):\n        assert parse_posted_at(\"\") is None\n        assert parse_posted_at(None) is None\n\n    def test_epoch_seconds(self):\n        dt = parse_posted_at(\"1700000000\")\n        assert dt.tzinfo == timezone.utc\n\n    def test_epoch_milliseconds(self):\n        # Lever-style 13-digit ms epoch\n        dt_ms = parse_posted_at(\"1700000000000\")\n        dt_s = parse_posted_at(\"1700000000\")\n        assert dt_ms == dt_s\n\n    def test_epoch_boundary_exact_1e12(self):\n        # 1_000_000_000_000 must be treated as ms, not s\n        dt = parse_posted_at(\"1000000000000\")\n        assert dt.year < 2100  # sanity: didn't parse as year-33658\n\n    def test_negative_epoch(self):\n        assert parse_posted_at(\"-100\") is not None\n\n    def test_iso_with_trailing_z(self):\n        dt = parse_posted_at(\"2024-01-15T10:00:00Z\")\n        assert dt.tzinfo == timezone.utc\n\n    def test_iso_naive_assumes_utc(self):\n        dt = parse_posted_at(\"2024-01-15T10:00:00\")\n        assert dt.tzinfo == timezone.utc\n\n    def test_unparseable_prose_returns_none(self):\n        assert parse_posted_at(\"Posted 3 Days Ago\") is None\n\n    def test_garbage_does_not_raise(self):\n        assert parse_posted_at(\"not a date at all\") is None\n\n\nclass TestJob:\n    def _job(self, **kw):\n        defaults = dict(source=\"greenhouse\", company=\"acme\", external_id=\"1\",\n                         title=\"Engineer\", url=\"https://x/1\")\n        return Job(**{**defaults, **kw})\n\n    def test_key_is_stable_and_unique(self):\n        j1 = self._job(external_id=\"1\")\n        j2 = self._job(external_id=\"2\")\n        assert j1.key != j2.key\n        assert j1.key == \"greenhouse:acme:1\"\n\n    def test_key_differs_across_sources_same_external_id(self):\n        j1 = self._job(source=\"greenhouse\", external_id=\"1\")\n        j2 = self._job(source=\"lever\", external_id=\"1\")\n        assert j1.key != j2.key\n\n    def test_content_hash_stable_across_irrelevant_field_changes(self):\n        j1 = self._job(posted_at=\"2024-01-01\", salary_range=\"$100k\")\n        j2 = self._job(posted_at=\"2024-06-01\", salary_range=\"$200k\")\n        assert j1.content_hash == j2.content_hash\n\n    def test_content_hash_changes_on_title_change(self):\n        j1 = self._job(title=\"Engineer I\")\n        j2 = self._job(title=\"Engineer II\")\n        assert j1.content_hash != j2.content_hash\n\n    def test_to_row_excludes_raw_includes_key_and_hash(self):\n        j = self._job(raw={\"secret\": \"blob\"})\n        row = j.to_row()\n        assert \"raw\" not in row\n        assert row[\"key\"] == j.key\n        assert row[\"content_hash\"] == j.content_hash\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. `filters.py`\n\n**Untested:** `match`, `filter_jobs`, `_compile`.\n\n**Edge cases missed:**\n- Word-boundary regex behavior: `include=[\"ML\"]` shouldn't match `\"HTML\"`, but `include=[\"ai\"]` matching `\"Air Traffic\"` because of `\\b` boundaries around substrings needs verification\n- `exclude` takes precedence over `include` (a job matching both should be dropped)\n- Case-insensitivity\n- Empty rules dict â†’ everything passes\n- `locations` filter uses substring match, not word-boundary â€” location `\"San Francisco, CA\"` vs filter `\"SF\"` should NOT match (good to lock this behavior in a test since it's a common false-negative complaint)\n- `cutoff` behavior with unparseable `posted_at` â€” spec says explicitly \"keep postings whose timestamp couldn't be parsed\" â€” this permissive behavior needs a dedicated test since it's a deliberate but non-obvious choice\n- `max_age_days` as float/fractional string from YAML\n\n```python\n# tests/test_filters.py\nimport pytest\nfrom datetime import datetime, timedelta, timezone\nfrom models import Job\nfrom filters import match, filter_jobs\n\n\ndef _job(**kw):\n    defaults = dict(source=\"greenhouse\", company=\"acme\", external_id=\"1\",\n                     title=\"Software Engineer\", url=\"https://x/1\",\n                     location=\"San Francisco, CA\", department=\"Engineering\")\n    return Job(**{**defaults, **kw})\n\n\nclass TestMatch:\n    def test_no_rules_passes(self):\n        assert match(_job()) is True\n\n    def test_include_keyword_hit(self):\n        assert match(_job(title=\"Senior ML Engineer\"), include=[\"ML\"]) is True\n\n    def test_include_keyword_miss(self):\n        assert match(_job(title=\"Sales Rep\"), include=[\"Engineer\"]) is False\n\n    def test_include_respects_word_boundary(self):\n        # \"ai\" should not match inside \"Maintain\"\n        assert match(_job(title=\"Maintainer\"), include=[\"ai\"]) is False\n\n    def test_exclude_overrides_include(self):\n        j = _job(title=\"Senior Manager Engineer\")\n        assert match(j, include=[\"Engineer\"], exclude=[\"Manager\"]) is False\n\n    def test_exclude_case_insensitive(self):\n        assert match(_job(title=\"INTERN role\"), exclude=[\"intern\"]) is False\n\n    def test_locations_substring_no_word_boundary(self):\n        # documents current behavior: \"SF\" as a bare substring filter\n        assert match(_job(location=\"San Francisco\"), locations=[\"Francisco\"]) is True\n        assert match(_job(location=\"San Francisco\"), locations=[\"SF\"]) is False\n\n    def test_cutoff_drops_old_parseable_job(self):\n        cutoff = datetime.now(timezone.utc) - timedelta(days=1)\n        old = (cutoff - timedelta(days=10)).isoformat()\n        assert match(_job(posted_at=old), cutoff=cutoff) is False\n\n    def test_cutoff_keeps_unparseable_posted_at(self):\n        cutoff = datetime.now(timezone.utc)\n        assert match(_job(posted_at=\"Posted 3 Days Ago\"), cutoff=cutoff) is True\n\n    def test_cutoff_keeps_recent_job(self):\n        cutoff = datetime.now(timezone.utc) - timedelta(days=30)\n        recent = datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat()\n        assert match(_job(posted_at=recent), cutoff=cutoff) is True\n\n\nclass TestFilterJobs:\n    def test_empty_rules_returns_all(self):\n        jobs = [_job(external_id=str(i)) for i in range(3)]\n        assert filter_jobs(jobs, {}) == jobs\n\n    def test_max_age_days_computes_cutoff(self):\n        jobs = [_job(posted_at=datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat())]\n        result = filter_jobs(jobs, {\"max_age_days\": 1})\n        assert result == jobs\n\n    def test_max_age_days_as_fractional_string_from_yaml(self):\n        jobs = [_job(posted_at=datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat())]\n        result = filter_jobs(jobs, {\"max_age_days\": \"0.5\"})\n        assert result == jobs\n\n    def test_combines_all_rule_types(self):\n        jobs = [\n            _job(external_id=\"1\", title=\"ML Engineer\", location=\"Remote\"),\n            _job(external_id=\"2\", title=\"Sales\", location=\"Remote\"),\n        ]\n        result = filter_jobs(jobs, {\"include_keywords\": [\"Engineer\"],\n                                     \"locations\": [\"Remote\"]})\n        assert [j.external_id for j in result] == [\"1\"]\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. `store.py` â€” needs an in-memory-DB integration test suite\n\n**Untested:** everything â€” `__init__`/schema creation, `_migrate`, `diff` (new/changed/unchanged branches), `get_meta`/`set_meta`, `added_since`, `count`, context manager protocol.\n\n**Edge cases / integration gaps:**\n- Re-opening a DB file that predates the `salary_range` column (the `_migrate` additive-column path) â€” needs a fixture that creates a DB with the old schema\n- `diff` called twice with identical jobs â†’ second call should report `new=[]`, `changed=[]`\n- `diff` where only `content_hash`-relevant fields changed vs. only cosmetic fields (e.g. `posted_at` bump alone) â†’ should NOT appear in `changed`\n- `added_since` ordering and the strict `>` (not `>=`) boundary â€” a row with `first_seen == ts` must be excluded\n- `set_meta` upsert (`ON CONFLICT`) â€” calling twice with same key updates rather than erroring\n- Concurrent-ish sequential `diff` calls across \"runs\" (simulating scheduled scrape behavior)\n\n```python\n# tests/test_store.py\nimport pytest\nimport sqlite3\nfrom store import Store\nfrom models import Job\n\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef store(tmp_path):\n    s = Store(tmp_path / \"test.db\")\n    yield s\n    s.close()\n\n\ndef _job(external_id=\"1\", title=\"Engineer\", **kw):\n    return Job(source=\"greenhouse\", company=\"acme\", external_id=external_id,\n               title=title, url=\"https://x/1\", **kw)\n\n\nclass TestSchemaAndMigration:\n    def test_creates_schema_on_fresh_db(self, tmp_path):\n        with Store(tmp_path / \"fresh.db\") as s:\n            assert s.count() == 0\n\n    def test_migrates_db_missing_salary_range_column(self, tmp_path):\n        path = tmp_path / \"old.db\"\n        conn = sqlite3.connect(str(path))\n        conn.executescript(\"\"\"\n            CREATE TABLE jobs (\n                key TEXT PRIMARY KEY, source TEXT, company TEXT,\n                external_id TEXT, title TEXT, url TEXT, location TEXT,\n                department TEXT, employment_type TEXT, posted_at TEXT,\n                content_hash TEXT, first_seen TEXT, last_seen TEXT\n            );\n        \"\"\")\n        conn.commit(); conn.close()\n\n        with Store(path) as s:\n            cols = {r[\"name\"] for r in s.conn.execute(\"PRAGMA table_info(jobs)\")}\n            assert \"salary_range\" in cols\n\n\nclass TestDiff:\n    def test_new_job_reported_as_new(self, store):\n        new, changed = store.diff([_job()])\n        assert len(new) == 1 and changed == []\n        assert store.count() == 1\n\n    def test_unchanged_job_on_second_run_is_neither_new_nor_changed(self, store):\n        store.diff([_job()])\n        new, changed = store.diff([_job()])\n        assert new == [] and changed == []\n\n    def test_material_change_detected(self, store):\n        store.diff([_job(title=\"Engineer I\")])\n        new, changed = store.diff([_job(title=\"Engineer II\")])\n        assert new == [] and len(changed) == 1\n\n    def test_cosmetic_only_change_not_flagged(self, store):\n        store.diff([_job(posted_at=\"2024-01-01\")])\n        new, changed = store.diff([_job(posted_at=\"2024-06-01\")])\n        assert new == [] and changed == []\n\n    def test_duplicate_key_within_same_batch_last_write_wins(self, store):\n        # two Job objects sharing (source, company, external_id) in one call\n        new, changed = store.diff([_job(title=\"A\"), _job(title=\"B\")])\n        assert store.count() == 1\n\n\nclass TestMeta:\n    def test_get_meta_missing_returns_none(self, store):\n        assert store.get_meta(\"last_scan\") is None\n\n    def test_set_then_get_meta(self, store):\n        store.set_meta(\"last_scan\", \"2024-01-01T00:00:00+00:00\")\n        assert store.get_meta(\"last_scan\") == \"2024-01-01T00:00:00+00:00\"\n\n    def test_set_meta_upserts(self, store):\n        store.set_meta(\"k\", \"v1\")\n        store.set_meta(\"k\", \"v2\")\n        assert store.get_meta(\"k\") == \"v2\"\n\n\nclass TestAddedSince:\n    def test_excludes_rows_at_exact_boundary(self, store, monkeypatch):\n        store.diff([_job(external_id=\"1\")])\n        ts = store.conn.execute(\n            \"SELECT first_seen FROM jobs WHERE external_id='1'\").fetchone()[0]\n        assert store.added_since(ts) == []\n\n    def test_orders_oldest_first(self, store):\n        store.diff([_job(external_id=\"1\"), _job(external_id=\"2\")])\n        rows = store.added_since(\"1970-01-01T00:00:00+00:00\")\n        assert len(rows) == 2\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. `pipeline.py`\n\n**Untested:** `load_config` (defaulting), `run` (dry_run vs persisted path, ordering of fetchâ†’filterâ†’dedupâ†’notify), `run_sync`.\n\n**Gaps:**\n- `load_config` defaults when keys are absent (`sources`, `filters`, `db`, `concurrency`)\n- `dry_run=True` must not touch the `Store` or call `dispatch` at all\n- `run()` should call `fetch_all`, `filter_jobs`, `store.diff`, `dispatch` in that order with correct args â€” this is an orchestration/integration test that needs mocking of `fetch_all` and `notify.dispatch`\n\n```python\n# tests/test_pipeline.py\nimport pytest\nfrom unittest.mock import AsyncMock, patch\nimport pipeline\n\n\ndef test_load_config_defaults(tmp_path):\n    cfg_path = tmp_path / \"sources.yaml\"\n    cfg_path.write_text(\"sources: []\\n\")\n    cfg = pipeline.load_config(cfg_path)\n    assert cfg[\"filters\"] == {}\n    assert cfg[\"db\"] == \"jobs.db\"\n    assert cfg[\"concurrency\"] == 8\n\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_dry_run_never_touches_store_or_dispatch(tmp_path):\n    cfg_path = tmp_path / \"sources.yaml\"\n    cfg_path.write_text(\"sources: []\\ndb: %s\\n\" % (tmp_path / \"jobs.db\"))\n    with patch(\"pipeline.fetch_all\", new=AsyncMock(return_value=[])), \\\n         patch(\"pipeline.Store\") as mock_store, \\\n         patch(\"pipeline.dispatch\") as mock_dispatch:\n        result = await pipeline.run(cfg_path, dry_run=True)\n    mock_store.assert_not_called()\n    mock_dispatch.assert_not_called()\n    assert result == {\"matched\": 0, \"new\": 0, \"changed\": 0}\n\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_run_persists_and_dispatches(tmp_path):\n    from models import Job\n    j = Job(source=\"greenhouse\", company=\"acme\", external_id=\"1\",\n            title=\"Engineer\", url=\"https://x/1\")\n    cfg_path = tmp_path / \"sources.yaml\"\n    cfg_path.write_text(\"sources: []\\ndb: %s\\n\" % (tmp_path / \"jobs.db\"))\n    with patch(\"pipeline.fetch_all\", new=AsyncMock(return_value=[j])), \\\n         patch(\"pipeline.dispatch\") as mock_dispatch:\n        result = await pipeline.run(cfg_path, dry_run=False)\n    assert result[\"new\"] == 1\n    mock_dispatch.assert_called_once()\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5. `notify.py`\n\n**Untested:** all six functions, plus `dispatch`'s failure isolation, which is the most important behavior here (one broken notifier must not block the others).\n\n**Edge cases / error-handling gaps:**\n- Each notifier's \"no-op unless env var set\" branch â€” none of these are tested for either the skip path or the active path\n- `notify_sms` raising on non-2xx Twilio response (`resp.raise_for_status()`) â€” must be caught by `dispatch`, not propagate\n- `_sms_body` truncation at `limit` and the `+N more` line\n- `dispatch` continuing to run remaining notifiers after one throws (currently *zero* coverage of this safety net â€” a regression here would be silent and severe)\n- `notify_email` SMTP auth only attempted when `SMTP_USER` is set\n\n```python\n# tests/test_notify.py\nimport pytest\nimport httpx\nimport respx\nfrom unittest.mock import patch, MagicMock\nfrom models import Job\nimport notify\n\n\ndef _job(**kw):\n    defaults = dict(source=\"greenhouse\", company=\"acme\", external_id=\"1\",\n                     title=\"Engineer\", url=\"https://x/1\")\n    return Job(**{**defaults, **kw})\n\n\nclass TestNotifyConsole:\n    def test_prints_no_fresh_listings_when_empty(self, capsys):\n        notify.notify_console([], [])\n        assert \"No fresh listings\" in capsys.readouterr().out\n\n    def test_prints_new_and_changed_sections(self, capsys):\n        notify.notify_console([_job()], [_job(external_id=\"2\")])\n        out = capsys.readouterr().out\n        assert \"NEW\" in out and \"UPDATED\" in out\n\n\nclass TestNotifySlack:\n    def test_noop_without_env_var(self, monkeypatch):\n        monkeypatch.delenv(\"SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL\", raising=False)\n        with patch(\"httpx.post\") as mock_post:\n            notify.notify_slack([_job()], [])\n        mock_post.assert_not_called()\n\n    def test_noop_when_no_jobs_even_with_url_set(self, monkeypatch):\n        monkeypatch.setenv(\"SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL\", \"https://hooks.slack.test/x\")\n        with patch(\"httpx.post\") as mock_post:\n            notify.notify_slack([], [])\n        mock_post.assert_not_called()\n\n    @respx.mock\n    def test_posts_when_configured(self, monkeypatch):\n        monkeypatch.setenv(\"SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL\", \"https://hooks.slack.test/x\")\n        route = respx.post(\"https://hooks.slack.test/x\").mock(\n            return_value=httpx.Response(200))\n        notify.notify_slack([_job()], [])\n        assert route.called\n\n\nclass TestNotifySms:\n    def test_body_truncates_at_limit_with_more_count(self):\n        jobs = [_job(external_id=str(i), title=f\"Role {i}\") for i in range(10)]\n        body = notify._sms_body(jobs, [], limit=8)\n        assert \"+2 more\" in body\n\n    def test_noop_missing_any_twilio_var(self, monkeypatch):\n        monkeypatch.setenv(\"TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID\", \"sid\")\n        monkeypatch.delenv(\"TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN\", raising=False)\n        with patch(\"httpx.post\") as mock_post:\n            notify.notify_sms([_job()], [])\n        mock_post.assert_not_called()\n\n    @respx.mock\n    def test_raises_on_twilio_error_response(self, monkeypatch):\n        for k, v in {\"TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID\": \"sid\", \"TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN\": \"tok\",\n                     \"TWILIO_FROM\": \"+1\", \"TWILIO_TO\": \"+2\"}.items():\n            monkeypatch.setenv(k, v)\n        respx.post(url__regex=r\".*api\\.twilio\\.com.*\").mock(\n            return_value=httpx.Response(400, json={\"message\": \"bad number\"}))\n        with pytest.raises(httpx.HTTPStatusError):\n            notify.notify_sms([_job()], [])\n\n\nclass TestDispatch:\n    def test_one_notifier_failure_does_not_block_others(self, capsys):\n        calls = []\n        def ok(new, changed): calls.append(\"ok\")\n        def boom(new, changed): raise RuntimeError(\"boom\")\n        with patch(\"notify.NOTIFIERS\", [boom, ok]):\n            notify.dispatch([_job()], [])\n        assert calls == [\"ok\"]\n        assert \"boom\" in capsys.readouterr().out\n```\n\n---\n\n### 6. `fetchers.py` â€” largest surface area, currently 0 coverage on 15 ATS integrations\n\nThis is the highest-risk gap: parsers are pure functions (trivial to test with fixture payloads) but are entirely untested, and the retry/pagination logic that wraps them is completely unverified.\n\n**Parser edge cases missed (per ATS), each needs a \"happy path\" + \"missing/null field\" fixture:**\n- `parse_greenhouse`: missing `location`/`departments` keys\n- `parse_lever`: `_lever_salary` â€” both `salaryRange` present, only `salaryDescriptionPlain` present, neither present\n- `parse_ashby`: `isListed: False` jobs must be filtered out; `id` vs `jobId` fallback\n- `parse_smartrecruiters`: partial location (missing city/region/country)\n- `parse_recruitee`: flat string location vs city/country assembly\n- `parse_workable`: dict location vs flat city/state/country; `shortcode` vs `id` fallback\n- `parse_google`: `_extract_ds1` regex fallback path when `sideChannel` key is absent; `_ds1_posted_at` index-out-of-range guard; job entry with falsy `j[0]`\n- `parse_deshaw`: duplicate `data-job-id` dedup via `seen`; missing `href` fallback URL\n- `parse_twosigma`: triple-rendered card dedup; `mloc` not found\n- `parse_optiver`: `href` prefix stripping (`join-us/jobs/` removal), absolute vs relative href\n- `parse_meta`: duplicate id dedup, empty `locations`/`teams`\n- `parse_microsoft`: `postedTs` missing â†’ `posted_at=\"\"`; `standardizedLocations` vs `locations` fallback\n- `parse_netflix`: `t_create` vs `t_update` fallback; comma-packed location expansion\n- `_amazon_posted_at`: malformed date string â†’ returns `\"\"` (ValueError/KeyError caught), unrecognized month name\n- `parse_amazon`: `id` vs `id_icims` fallback, missing `job_path` â†’ empty url\n\n**Retry/pagination logic (needs `respx` + mocked `httpx.AsyncClient`), fully untested:**\n- `_request` retries on 429/500/502/503/504, gives up after `retries` attempts and raises `RuntimeError`\n- `_request` does NOT retry on 404 (non-retryable `HTTPStatusError` from `raise_for_status`) â€” actually check: 404 isn't in the retryable tuple so `raise_for_status()` raises immediately, uncaught by the `except` clause's retry loop... wait it IS caught by `except (httpx.TransportError, httpx.HTTPStatusError)` â€” so it retries `retries` times before giving up. Worth pinning down with a test since it's non-obvious.\n- Pagination loops (`fetch_twosigma`, `fetch_optiver`, `fetch_google`, `fetch_microsoft`, `fetch_netflix`, `fetch_amazon`, `fetch_workday`) â€” stop-on-empty-fresh-batch logic, `max_pages` safety cap, dedup via `seen` across pages\n- `fetch_workday`: `offset >= total` termination and the `offset > 5000` safety cap\n- `fetch_meta`: `\"for (;;);\"` JSDS prefix stripping; `data.get(\"errors\")` â†’ raises `RuntimeError` (simulates rotated doc_id)\n- `fetch_source`: unknown ATS raises `ValueError` with the known-ATS list\n- `fetch_all`: one source failing doesn't kill the others (`except Exception` inside `one()`); concurrency semaphore actually caps in-flight requests; client is closed only when `fetch_all` created it (`owns_client`) â€” passing an external client must NOT close it\n\n```python\n# tests/test_fetchers.py\nimport pytest\nimport httpx\nimport respx\nfrom fetchers import (\n    parse_greenhouse, parse_lever, _lever_salary, parse_ashby,\n    parse_google, _extract_ds1, _ds1_posted_at, parse_deshaw,\n    parse_twosigma, parse_optiver, parse_meta, parse_microsoft,\n    parse_netflix, parse_amazon, _amazon_posted_at,\n    fetch_source, fetch_all, _request,\n)\n\n\nclass TestParseGreenhouse:\n    def test_missing_location_and_departments(self):\n        jobs = parse_greenhouse(\"acme\", {\"jobs\": [{\"id\": 1, \"title\": \"Eng\"}]})\n        assert jobs[0].location == \"\" and jobs[0].department == \"\"\n\n\nclass TestLeverSalary:\n    def test_range_present(self):\n        assert _lever_salary({\"salaryRange\": {\"min\": 100000, \"max\": 150000,\n                                               \"currency\": \"USD\"}}) == \"USD 100,000â€“150,000\"\n\n    def test_falls_back_to_description(self):\n        assert _lever_salary({\"salaryDescriptionPlain\": \"Competitive\"}) == \"Competitive\"\n\n    def test_neither_present(self):\n        assert _lever_salary({}) == \"\"\n\n\nclass TestParseAshby:\n    def test_unlisted_jobs_filtered(self):\n        jobs = parse_ashby(\"acme\", {\"jobs\": [\n            {\"id\": \"1\", \"title\": \"A\", \"isListed\": False},\n            {\"id\": \"2\", \"title\": \"B\", \"isListed\": True},\n        ]})\n        assert [j.external_id for j in jobs] == [\"2\"]\n\n\nclass TestGoogleDs1:\n    def test_extract_missing_sidechannel_falls_back(self):\n        html = \"key: 'ds:1', ..., data:[[[\\\"1\\\",\\\"Title\\\"]]]);\"\n        assert _extract_ds1(html) != []\n\n    def test_extract_no_match_returns_empty(self):\n        assert _extract_ds1(\"<html>nothing</html>\") == []\n\n    def test_posted_at_missing_timestamp_indices(self):\n        assert _ds1_posted_at([\"1\"]) == \"\"\n\n    def test_parse_google_skips_falsy_entries(self):\n        assert parse_google(\"google\", [None, [\"\"]]) == []\n\n\nclass TestAmazonPostedAt:\n    @pytest.mark.parametrize(\"value,expected_prefix\", [\n        (\"June 26, 2026\", \"2026-06-26\"),\n    ])\n    def test_valid_date(self, value, expected_prefix):\n        assert _amazon_posted_at(value).startswith(expected_prefix)\n\n    def test_malformed_date_returns_empty(self):\n        assert _amazon_posted_at(\"not a date\") == \"\"\n\n    def test_unknown_month_returns_empty(self):\n        assert _amazon_posted_at(\"Fooember 1, 2024\") == \"\"\n\n\nclass TestFetchSource:\n    @pytest.mark.asyncio\n    async def test_unknown_ats_raises(self):\n        async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n            with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"unknown ATS\"):\n                await fetch_source(client, {\"ats\": \"bogus\"})\n\n\nclass TestRequestRetry:\n    @respx.mock\n    @pytest.mark.asyncio\n    async def test_retries_on_503_then_succeeds(self):\n        route = respx.get(\"https://x.test/jobs\").mock(side_effect=[\n            httpx.Response(503), httpx.Response(200, json={\"jobs\": []}),\n        ])\n        async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n            r = await _request(client, \"https://x.test/jobs\", retries=3)\n        assert r.status_code == 200\n        assert route.call_count == 2\n\n    @respx.mock\n    @pytest.mark.asyncio\n    async def test_gives_up_after_max_retries(self):\n        respx.get(\"https://x.test/jobs\").mock(return_value=httpx.Response(500))\n        async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n            with pytest.raises(RuntimeError, match=\"failed to fetch\"):\n                await _request(client, \"https://x.test/jobs\", retries=2)\n\n\nclass TestFetchAll:\n    @pytest.mark.asyncio\n    async def test_one_source_failing_does_not_kill_others(self, capsys):\n        async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n            sources = [{\"ats\": \"bogus\", \"company\": \"x\"},\n                       {\"ats\": \"greenhouse\", \"company\": \"y\"}]\n            with respx.mock:\n                respx.get(url__regex=r\".*boards-api\\.greenhouse\\.io.*\").mock(\n                    return_value=httpx.Response(200, json={\"jobs\": []}))\n                jobs = await fetch_all(sources, client=client)\n        assert jobs == []\n        assert \"failed\" in capsys.readouterr().out\n\n    @pytest.mark.asyncio\n    async def test_external_client_not_closed(self):\n        client = httpx.AsyncClient()\n        await fetch_all([], client=client)\n        assert not client.is_closed\n        await client.aclose()\n```\n\nAlso worth a **pagination-specific** test class per multi-page fetcher (e.g. `fetch_optiver`, `fetch_workday`) mocking two pages of `respx` responses and asserting: (a) results from both pages are merged, (b) loop stops when a page returns no *fresh* ids even if the payload isn't empty (simulates server-side duplicate padding), (c) `max_pages` cap is respected even if the server never returns empty.\n\n---\n\n### 7. `agent.py` â€” deterministic helpers only (skip the Claude-launcher glue)\n\n**Untested and worth covering** (`cmd_db_new`, `cmd_db_mark`, `_normalize_ats`, `_chrome_bin`, `cmd_pdf_render`'s failure path):\n\n- `cmd_db_new` first-run path (no marker) uses `--since-days` window; subsequent runs use the stored marker\n- Truncation logic: `jobs`/`watermark` only advances at `first_seen` group boundaries â€” a batch mid-group must not be split (this is explicitly called out in a comment as a correctness invariant and has zero test coverage)\n- `cmd_db_mark` rejects a non-ISO watermark (exit code 2) and accepts `--now`\n- `_normalize_ats`: replacements skip `<style>`/`<script>` contents and skip inside tag attributes, only applying to text nodes\n- `cmd_pdf_render`: missing input file â†’ exit 2; Chrome producing non-PDF output â†’ exit 1\n\n```python\n# tests/test_agent.py\nimport pytest\nfrom datetime import datetime, timedelta, timezone\nfrom store import Store\nfrom models import Job\nimport agent\n\n\ndef _job(external_id, **kw):\n    return Job(source=\"greenhouse\", company=\"acme\", external_id=external_id,\n               title=\"Eng\", url=\"https://x/1\", **kw)\n\n\nclass TestDbNewMark:\n    def test_first_run_uses_since_days_window(self, tmp_path, capsys):\n        db_path = tmp_path / \"jobs.db\"\n        cfg = tmp_path / \"sources.yaml\"\n        cfg.write_text(f\"db: {db_path}\\n\")\n        with Store(db_path) as s:\n            s.diff([_job(\"1\")])\n        agent.cmd_db_new([\"-c\", str(cfg), \"--since-days\", \"1\"])\n        import json\n        out = json.loads(capsys.readouterr().out)\n        assert out[\"first_run\"] is True\n        assert out[\"count\"] == 1\n\n    def test_mark_rejects_non_iso_watermark(self, tmp_path, capsys):\n        db_path = tmp_path / \"jobs.db\"\n        cfg = tmp_path / \"sources.yaml\"\n        cfg.write_text(f\"db: {db_path}\\n\")\n        rc = agent.cmd_db_mark([\"not-a-date\", \"-c\", str(cfg)])\n        assert rc == 2\n\n    def test_mark_now_then_db_new_reports_since_marker(self, tmp_path, capsys):\n        db_path = tmp_path / \"jobs.db\"\n        cfg = tmp_path / \"sources.yaml\"\n        cfg.write_text(f\"db: {db_path}\\n\")\n        agent.cmd_db_mark([\"--now\", \"-c\", str(cfg)])\n        capsys.readouterr()\n        agent.cmd_db_new([\"-c\", str(cfg)])\n        import json\n        out = json.loads(capsys.readouterr().out)\n        assert out[\"first_run\"] is False\n\n\nclass TestNormalizeAts:\n    def test_skips_style_and_script_blocks(self):\n        html = \"<style>.x::before{content:'\\u2014'}</style><p>a \\u2014 b</p>\"\n        out, counts = agent._normalize_ats(html)\n        assert \"\\u2014\" not in out.split(\"</style>\")[1] or True  # style untouched\n        assert \"content:'\\u2014'\" in out  # style block preserved verbatim\n        assert \" - \" in out  # body text converted\n\n    def test_counts_em_dash_replacements(self):\n        out, counts = agent._normalize_ats(\"<p>a \\u2014 b \\u2014 c</p>\")\n        assert counts[\"em-dash\"] == 2\n\n    def test_does_not_touch_tag_attributes(self):\n        html = '<a title=\"x\\u2014y\">text</a>'\n        out, _ = agent._normalize_ats(html)\n        assert 'title=\"x\\u2014y\"' in out  # attribute preserved, not \"fixed\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### 8. `cli.py`\n\nThin wrapper â€” one integration test is enough:\n```python\n# tests/test_cli.py\nfrom unittest.mock import patch\nimport cli\n\ndef test_main_dry_run_forwards_flag():\n    with patch(\"cli.run_sync\") as mock_run:\n        with patch(\"sys.argv\", [\"cli.py\", \"-c\", \"sources.yaml\", \"--dry-run\"]):\n            cli.main()\n    mock_run.assert_called_once_with(\"sources.yaml\", dry_run=True)\n```\n\n---\n\n### Priority order if you're tackling this incrementally\n1. `models.py` + `filters.py` â€” pure, fast, highest bug-catching ROI, no infra needed beyond plain `pytest`.\n2. `store.py` â€” needs only `tmp_path`, no mocking; the `diff` unchanged/changed/new branches and the migration path are the riskiest untested logic in the repo (silent dedup bugs are hard to notice in prod).\n3. `fetchers.py` parsers â€” pure functions, just need fixture payloads per ATS; protects against the frequent \"ATS changed its JSON shape\" failure mode this codebase is clearly prone to (see the Meta doc_id rotation comment).\n4. `notify.py` `dispatch` isolation â€” small but critical safety net, currently unverified.\n5. `fetchers.py` retry/pagination + `pipeline.py`/`agent.py` orchestration â€” needs `respx`/`pytest-asyncio`, more setup cost, do last.\n",
